Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper focuses on nearest neighbor search in multimedia retrieval applications, which is a core problem in information retrieval. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper involves cross-modal retrieval across image and text modalities, which is a common problem in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimedia retrieval applications and cross-modal hashing, which are both relevant to the multimedia field. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach to improve indexing accuracy and efficiency, which falls under the machine learning domain. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper involves text retrieval and cross-modal retrieval, which are both relevant to the computation and language field.
